name: ANOA (BUBALUS)
description:
Anoa is the largest and endemic mammal that lives on the mainland of Sulawesi Island and Buton Island. Many call anoa a dwarf buffalo. Anoa is an animal belonging to the transitional fauna. Anoa is a mammal belonging to the Bovidae family which is spread almost all over the island
